{
  "answer": "**Viṣṇu Smṛti chapter 3 outlines the general duties of a king (*rājadharma*), such as protecting the people, establishing social orders, administration, taxation, military policy, and personal conduct, but it does not describe a \"daily routine\" (e.g., no mentions of waking, morning/evening rituals, or a timed schedule).**[^1]\n\nIf you're thinking of a king's daily schedule (e.g., rising at dawn or evening consultations), that appears in other Smṛtis like *Manusmṛti* chapter 7, but not here.[^2]\n\n[^1]: *Viṣṇu Smṛti*, Chapter 3, [translation](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/03/translation/).\n\n[^2]: This is based on a full-text search of the Falsafa corpus; no matching content exists in Viṣṇu Smṛti chapter 3.",
